Installation and Configuration
Prerequisites
You need Python 3.x installed on your Raspberry Pi (or other host machine).

Dependencies
This project requires the following Python libraries:

Bash

flask
requests
telnetlib
json
os
threading
feedparser
geopy 
Installation
Clone the Repository:

Bash

git clone https://github.com/YourUsername/radio-spo-watcher-dx.git
cd radio-spo-watcher-dx
Install Dependencies:

Bash

pip install -r requirements.txt

Configuration initiale
Before execution, you must modify the core configuration section in webapp.py:

Open webapp.py

Update the following constants:

Python

# webapp.py
MY_CALL = "YOUR_CALLSIGN"  # <-- Essential
WEB_PORT = 8000
QRA_DEFAULT = "JN33"  # <-- Your default QRA (for distance calculations)

# Telnet DX Cluster Configuration (Example)
TELNET_HOST = "cluster.example.com"
TELNET_PORT = 73
Launch
Ensure all dependencies are installed and configuration is complete.

Launch the application using the startup script:

./start.sh

Interface Usage Guide
1. Set Your QRA Locator
In the COMMAND DECK control panel:

Enter your QRA Locator (e.g., JN33, JN33BB).

Click on GO.

The system will center the map and update all distance calculations based on your location.

2. Watchlist Management
Enter a call sign (e.g., K1TTT) in the WATCHLIST field and click ADD.

Spots for this call sign will be highlighted in yellow and trigger a voice alert (if VOICE: ON).

3. Alert Systems
SURGE: A banner appears when a significant burst of activity is detected on a specific band.

OUVERTURE DETECTEE (OPENING DETECTED): The PROPAGATION HISTORY panel visually alerts if the Magic Bands (12m/10m/6m) are actively open.

